&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34);   text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;As we know that&lt;strong&gt; the main clause&lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;em&gt;Justin Bieber&amp;rsquo;s performance was given a standing ovation by the&amp;nbsp;people)&lt;/em&gt; of the sentence is in the&lt;strong&gt; past tense&lt;/strong&gt;, hence the &lt;strong&gt;subordinate clause&lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;em&gt;who has come to hear him&lt;/em&gt;)&amp;nbsp;should also be in the&lt;strong&gt; past form.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34);   text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the error is in &lt;strong&gt;part C&lt;/strong&gt; of the sentence, where &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;has come&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is replaced by &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;had come&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence is&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Justin Bieber&amp;rsquo;s performance was given&amp;nbsp;a standing ovation by the people who &lt;strong&gt;had come&lt;/strong&gt; to hear him.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&amp;nbsp;clause&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a group of words containing a subject and predicate and functioning as a member of a complex or compound sentence. Clauses are mainly of two types:&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An&amp;nbsp;independent clause&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;functions on its own to make a meaningful&amp;nbsp;sentence&amp;nbsp;and looks much like a regular sentence.&lt;br /&gt;
		In a sentence two independent clauses can be connected by the&amp;nbsp;coordinators:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;and, but, so, or, nor.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex:&lt;/strong&gt; He is a wise man.&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&amp;nbsp;dependent clause&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;cannot function on its own because it leaves an idea or thought unfinished. It is also called a subordinate clause. Dependent clauses help the independent clauses complete the sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex:&lt;/strong&gt; He bought a car&amp;nbsp;which was too expensive.&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39; i.e. &amp;#39;Serious&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Earnest: Resulting from or showing sincere and intense conviction (गंभीर).
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Example: He made an earnest attempt to improve his grades.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Serious: Solemn or thoughtful in character or manner (गंभीर).
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Example: She gave him a serious look.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Valiant (वीर): Possessing or showing courage or determination.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Example: The valiant soldier fought bravely.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Stupendous (विस्मयकारी): Extremely impressive.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Example: The magician performed a stupendous trick.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Careless (लापरवाह): Not giving sufficient attention or thought to avoiding harm or errors.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: He was careless with his responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;grammar.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Grammar&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;is a system of rules that allow us to structure sentences. It includes several aspects of the English language, like: (नियमों की एक प्रणाली जो हमें वाक्यों की संरचना करने की अनुमति देती है। इसमें अंग्रेजी भाषा के कई पहलू शामिल हैं, जैसे)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parts of speech&lt;/strong&gt; (verbs, adjectives, nouns, adverbs, prepositions, conjunctions, modifiers, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clauses&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g. independent, dependent, compound)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Punctuation&lt;/strong&gt; (like commas, semicolons, and periods &amp;mdash; when applied to usage)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;All the other given spellings are incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correctly spelt word is &lt;b&gt;grammar.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct answer choice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;painted&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrases like &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;How long is it since&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;It is one year since&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;, &amp;#39;It has been one year since&amp;#39; always take &lt;strong&gt;simple past tense&lt;/strong&gt; with them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure&lt;/strong&gt; for simple past tense:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Subject + the second form of verb + object
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;He played cricket yesterday.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct answer:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;em&gt;How long is it since you&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;painted&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; a landscape?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simple past tense:&lt;/strong&gt; It is used to express an action that started in the past, finished in the past and has no relation with the present.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Take a risk&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;throw caution to the wind&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to act in a reckless manner or to take a risk without worrying about the consequences. (जोखिम उठाना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Despite the risks, she decided to throw caution to the wind and invest all her savings in the new business venture.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Take a risk&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to doing something that involves potential danger or loss but might also lead to a significant gain. (जोखिम उठाना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;He took a risk by quitting his stable job to start his own company.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1 i.e. Take a risk.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;but&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Replace &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;so&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;with &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;but&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;to make the sentence correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We use &lt;strong&gt;so &lt;/strong&gt;as a subordinating conjunction to introduce clauses of result or decision.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example -&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;I got here late. It was a long journey, &lt;strong&gt;so &lt;/strong&gt;I&amp;#39;m really tired now.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;But&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;used to introduce an added statement, usually something that is different from what you have said before.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example -&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;She&amp;#39;s very hard-working &lt;strong&gt;but &lt;/strong&gt;not very imaginative.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, according to the given sentence, &lt;strong&gt;one cannot be stupid and proud of his/her stupidity at the same time.&amp;nbsp;But is used to connect ideas that contrast.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 4&lt;/strong&gt; is the appropriate option to substitute the underlined segment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improved sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Are you trying to say that you are stupid &lt;u&gt;but&lt;/u&gt; proud of it?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We use &lt;strong&gt;so that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in order that to talk about purpose. We often use them with modal verbs (can, would, will, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We often use&lt;strong&gt; though&lt;/strong&gt; to introduce a fact which you regard as less important than the fact in the main clause.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/confusion-points-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Confusion Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;But&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; indicates a complete negation and is usually used after a comma, in the middle of a sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Though&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; is usually used at the end of a sentence and indicates a partial negation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The idiom with a false meaning is: &lt;strong&gt;Take it with a grain of salt - To fully believe something.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct meaning of the idiom &amp;quot;Take it with a grain of salt&amp;quot; is to not fully believe or accept something as completely true or accurate.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It suggests being sceptical or cautious about the information received.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, option 1 is the idiom with false meaning, as it incorrectly states that the idiom means to fully believe something.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is - &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Instead of&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type:square;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the given options, the most appropriate answer is &amp;quot;Instead of&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As its meaning fits with the context correctly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Instead of &lt;/strong&gt;means &lt;strong&gt;an alternative of something or someone&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example - Instead of being happy he is indignant at my offer.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Instead of&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;attending the class, he was listening to the cricket commentary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the correct option is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;wise&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;prudent&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means acting with or showing care and thought for the future. (सावधान)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;It was prudent to save money for emergencies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Wise&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to having or showing experience, knowledge, and good judgment. (बुद्धिमान)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Her wise decision helped the company avoid a financial crisis.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the meaning of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;prudent&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is closest to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;wise&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;wise&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reckless &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;लापरवाह&lt;/span&gt;): Without thinking or caring about the consequences of an action.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His reckless driving led to a serious accident.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hasty &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;जल्दबाज़ी&lt;/span&gt;): Done or acting with excessive speed or urgency; hurried.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She made a hasty decision without considering all the facts.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Foolish&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;मूर्ख&lt;/span&gt;): Lacking good sense or judgment; unwise.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; It was foolish of him to invest all his money in one stock.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is- &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;insignificant&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given word&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;prominent&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;(adjective): very well known and important. (बहुत प्रसिद्ध और महत्वपूर्ण।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The government should be playing a more &lt;strong&gt;prominent &lt;/strong&gt;role in promoting human rights.​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;insignificant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;adjective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;not important or thought to be valuable. (महत्वपूर्ण नहीं है या मूल्यवान नहीं माना जाता है।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Her problems seemed pretty &lt;strong&gt;insignificant &lt;/strong&gt;compared to her brother&amp;rsquo;s.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;insignificant&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the most appropriate antonym for&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;prominent&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s explore the meaning of other options&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;bold&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;adjective&lt;/span&gt;): not shy, especially in a way that shows no respect. (शर्मीली नहीं, विशेष रूप से इस तरह से जो कोई सम्मान नहीं दिखाती है।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;He was a &lt;strong&gt;bold &lt;/strong&gt;and defiant little boy.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;catchy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;adjective&lt;/span&gt;): pleasing and easy to remember. (सुखद और याद रखने में आसान।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;a &lt;strong&gt;catchy &lt;/strong&gt;name.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;flamboyant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;adjective&lt;/span&gt;): very confident in your behaviour, and liking to be noticed by other people, for example because of the way you dress, talk, etc.. (अपने व्यवहार में बहुत विश्वास है, और अन्य लोगों द्वारा देखा जाना पसंद करते हैं, उदाहरण के लिए जिस तरह से आप कपड़े पहनते हैं, बात करते हैं, आदि।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The writer&amp;#39;s &lt;strong&gt;flamboyant &lt;/strong&gt;lifestyle was well known.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
